text:
(1) Hunter College (Bronx); W.P.A. men are shown working on the site of the College's new Bronx center on the west side of Jerome Avenue, north of E. 195th Street. The elevated trestle of the I.R.T. subway appears on the right.

January 6, 1937

W.P.A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project

(2) Viewing northeastward across the campus from near Paul Avenue. In the left background is visible De Witt Clinton High School, and in the center are the chimney stacks of the City-Owned and I.R.T. subway car yards.

May 10, 1937

W.P.A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project

(3) The entrance to the campus at Paul Avenue.

1937

W.P.A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project
title: Colleges and Universities - Hunter College - Bronx.
